IRS990.MissionDesc: TO PROVIDE LOW-INCOME ELDERLY & HANDICAPPED PERSONS WITH AFFORDABLE HOUSING FACILITIES & SERVICES SPECIALLY DESIGNED TO MEET THEIR PHYSICAL, SOCIAL & PSYCHOLOGICAL NEEDS, AND TO PROMOTE THEIR HEALTH, SECURITY, HAPPINESS & USEFULNESS IN LONGER LIVING ON A NONPROFIT BASIS.
IRS990.Desc: THE CORPORATION WAS ORGANIZED TO PROVIDE RENTAL HOUSING FOR LOW AND MODERATE-INCOME ELDERLY PERSONS. IT OWNS AND OPERATES AN AFFORDABLE HOUSING PROJECT CONSISTING OF A TOTAL OF 150 RENTAL UNITS FOR LOW-INCOME SENIORS IN NEWARK, CALIFORNIA. THE PROJECT IS REGULATED BY HUD AS TO RENT CHARGES, OPERATING METHODS AND OTHER MATTERS UNDER SECTION 202 OF THE NATIONAL HOUSING ACT AND UNDER SECTION 207 PURSUANT TO SECTION 223(f) OF THE NATIONAL HOUSING ACT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CORPORATION HAS BEEN GRANTED TAX-EXEMPT STATUS BY THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE UNDER CODE SECTION 501(C)(3) AND BY THE CALIFORNIA FRANCHISE TAX BOARD UNDER CODE SECTION 23701(D). THE CORPORATION BELIEVES THAT IT DOES NOT HAVE ANY UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS THAT ARE MATERIAL TO THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE FEDERAL AND STATE INFORMATION RETURNS FOR THE YEARS ENDING SEPTEMBER 30, 2017, 2016, 2015 AND 2014 ARE SUBJECT TO EXAMINATION BY REGULATORY AGENCIES, GENERALLY FOR THREE YEARS AND FOUR YEARS AFTER THEY WERE FILED FOR THE FEDERAL AND STATE RETURNS, RESPECTIVELY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 3: Description of Delegated Duties to Management Company
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE PROJECT IS MANAGED BY SATELLITE AFFORDABLE HOUSING ASSOCIATES PROPERTY MANAGEMENT (SAHA PM), A NONPROFIT PUBLIC BENEFIT CORPORATION RELATED TO THE CORPORATION BY COMMON MEMBERS OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS AND/OR THE POWER TO APPOINT DIRECTORS. SAHA PM IS RESPONSIBLE FOR THE DAY TO DAY OPERATIONS OF THE LOW INCOME HOUSING PROJECT, INCLUDING MAINTENANCE OF ACCOUNTING RECORDS, RENT COLLECTION, FACILITY MAINTENANCE, ETC.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 11b: Form 990 Review Process
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 IS REVIEWED BY THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR OF SATELLITE AFFORDABLE HOUSING ASSOCIATES, A RELATED CALIFORNIA NON-PROFIT PUBLIC BENEFIT CORPORATION, AND SIGNED BY THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 12c: Explanation of Monitoring and Enforcement of Conflicts
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Annually, a conflict of interest disclosure form is distributed to each board member to complete and sign. These are reviewed for any conflicts of interest and kept on file.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 15a: Compensation Review & Approval Process - CEO, Top Management
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CORPORATION DOES NOT PAY COMPENSATION, EITHER AS AN EMPLOYEE OR INDEPENDENT CONTRACTOR, TO THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR OR ANY OFFICER.THE CORPORATION'S EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND DIRECTOR OF FINANCE ARE COMPENSATED EMPLOYEES OF SATELLITE AFFORDABLE HOUSING ASSOCIATES (SAHA), A RELATED CALIFORNIA NONPROFIT PUBLIC BENEFIT CORPORATION. THEIR SALARIES FROM SAHA ARE SUBJECT TO ANNUAL REVIEW BY SAHA'S BOARD OF DIRECTORS AND THE BOARD DETERMINES THE SALARIES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 15b: Compensation Review and Approval Process for Officers and Key Employees
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CORPORATION DOES NOT PAY COMPENSATION, EITHER AS AN EMPLOYEE OR INDEPENDENT CONTRACTOR, TO ANY INDIVIDUAL.THE CORPORATION'S EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND DIRECTOR OF FINANCE ARE COMPENSATED EMPLOYEES OF SATELLITE AFFORDABLE HOUSING ASSOCIATES (SAHA), A RELATED CALIFORNIA NONPROFIT PUBLIC BENEFIT CORPORATION. THEIR SALARIES FROM SAHA ARE SUBJECT TO ANNUAL REVIEW BY SAHA'S BOARD OF DIRECTORS AND THE BOARD DETERMINES THE SALARIES.
